ce:section.ce:para:
The applicability of the ratiometric fluorescence method for Co2+ detection in real water samples was assessed through recovery studies. Known concentrations of Co2+ were spiked into several water samples before analysis. The measured Co2+ concentrations showed good recovery in the range of 96.30 % − 101.80 % of the spiked amounts (
                           Table 1

                           ). The relative standard deviations were less than 3.18 % across the tested samples. These results validate the accuracy of the ratiometric sensing technique for quantifying Co2+ in complex environmental water matrices. The reliable recoveries and low standard deviations demonstrate the method's precision and lack of matrix interferences. The results obtained from the sensing platform agree with those obtained using another reliable reported fluorometric method [46]. This consistency indicates that the sensing platform offers reliable accuracy and precision for the quantitative determination of cobalt ions in river water and tap water samples.
